.TH GILDER-CONVERT 1 "2026-06-18" "Gilder" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gilder-convert \- convert and pack Gilder wallpaper packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gilder-convert pack
.I source.gwpdir dest.gwp
.br
.B gilder-convert unpack
.I source.gwp dest.gwpdir
.br
.B gilder-convert wallpaper-engine
.I source-project-dir dest.gwpdir
.br
.B gilder-convert wallpaper-engine --pack
.I source-project-dir dest.gwp
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gilder-convert
packs and unpacks Gilder wallpaper packages and converts local Wallpaper Engine
projects into Gilder packages.
.PP
Wallpaper Engine conversion currently supports static image, video, web,
conservative scene-lite, and playlist/collection projects. Custom shader
effects are reported as conversion gaps rather than executed or translated into
native shader entries. Executable application projects are reported clearly in
.I metadata/conversion-report.json
and are not executed.
.SH OUTPUT
Converted projects contain
.I manifest.gilder.json
plus copied assets, previews, and metadata. Missing previews are generated from
static source images when possible. Large static raster images use
.B ffprobe
and
.B ffmpeg
from
.I PATH
to generate 16:9, ultrawide, and portrait resolution variants when possible. Video projects without
previews use
.B ffmpeg
from
.I PATH
to generate first-frame poster and thumbnail images, then fall back to a
metadata-based SVG preview if extraction is unavailable or fails.
.PP
.B pack
accepts directory packages with either
.I manifest.gilder.json
or
.I manifest.gilder.toml
and writes canonical
.I manifest.gilder.json
into
.I .gwp
archives.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gilderd (1),
.BR gilderctl (1)
